-# GitHub Policy Pack (V6 Command-Law Surface)
+# GitHub Policy Pack
 
-Bu doküman V6 için GitHub tarafını policy as code olarak nasıl kilitli tuttuğumuzu tanımlar.
+Status: `RELEASE_BLOCKED`
 
-## Required policy surface
+This document defines the GitHub governance surface for Pala OS v6. GitHub is the operational source of record, but GitHub state is not enough to release. Court, evidence, source-chain, and owner approval still control release.
 
-- `main` branch branch-protection
-- PR onayı + status checks
-- CODEOWNERS review sınırı
-- PR/Issue template zorunluluğu
-- Actions ile gece-nöbeti (cron) çalıştırımı
+## Enforcement Target
 
-## Branch settings checklist
+Primary target:
 
-- Require pull request before merging `main`
-- Dismiss stale reviews on new commits
-- Require at least one approved review for merges
-- Restrict who can push to protected branch (`@trugurpala` and approved owners)
-- Enforce linear history on protected branches
-- Do not allow bypass of checks for non-bot actors
+- Repository: `trugurpala/pala-os-v6`
+- Default branch: `main`
+- Required posture: protected by branch protection or an active repository ruleset
 
-## Workflow checklist (repo current)
+Fallback:
 
-- `test` job: node bootstrap, node test, status check
-- `nightly-cron` job: schedule + `sak cron run`
-- `npm test` as baseline proof command; active V6 tests stay scoped to `test/`, while `legacy/` remains quarantine reference material
-- `node src/cli.js status` and `bak` calls before release
-- `npm run github:audit` reads branch protection and latest Actions state when GitHub CLI authentication exists
+- If repository rulesets are unavailable, use branch protection on `main`.
+- If branch protection readback is unavailable, report `NOT_AVAILABLE_WITH_REASON`.
+- If neither branch protection nor an active ruleset is proven, report `BRANCH_PROTECTION_BLOCKED`.
 
-## Evidence requirements
+## Required Branch Rules
 
-- PR template has:
-  - Evidence checkboxes
-  - Dashboard state check
-  - Source-card check when external code is involved
-- Release issue form requires:
-  - Evidence text
-  - Owner approval state
-  - Rollback note
+`main` must enforce:
 
-## Governance lock
+- Require pull request before merge.
+- Require at least one approving review.
+- Require CODEOWNERS review.
+- Dismiss stale approvals when new commits are pushed.
+- Require status checks before merge.
+- Require conversation resolution when available.
+- Block force pushes.
+- Block branch deletion.
+- Prefer linear history when it does not create owner deadlock.
 
-- `Release`, `push`, `core overwrite`, and policy edits remain owner-locked via court flow.
+## Required Checks
+
+Initial required remote check:
+
+- `test`
+
+Phase B workflow stabilizes these additional local job names:
+
+- `source-court-audit`
+- `legacy-boundary`
+- `court`
+
+These extra jobs become required only after they exist on GitHub and their check-run names are proven by readback. `nightly-cron` is schedule-only and must not be a required PR check.
+
+## CODEOWNERS Policy
+
+Governance-critical paths must be owner-controlled:
+
+- `.github/**`
+- `src/**`
+- `scripts/**`
+- `test/**`
+- `docs/**`
+- `Dockerfile`
+- `compose.yaml`
+- `package.json`
+- `AGENTS.md`
+- `README.md`
+- `PALA_RULES.md`
+- `SECURITY.md`
+- `ARCHITECTURE.md`
+
+## PR Review Package
+
+Every implementation PR must include:
+
+1. Implementation Report.
+2. Changed Files Manifest.
+3. Repo Change Review.
+4. Raw Patch/Diff, or `NOT_AVAILABLE_WITH_REASON`.
+
+No Review Package = No Court Decision.
+
+If these artefacts are missing, the phase is at most `PARTIAL`; it cannot be marked `PASS`.
+
+## Solo-Owner Deadlock Risk
+
+This repo may be operated by a single owner account. If GitHub prevents the PR author from approving their own PR and no second reviewer exists, strict review can create a merge deadlock.
+
+Risk status:
+
+- Governance target remains required.
+- The risk must be reported as `PARTIAL` until a second approved reviewer/team or documented owner emergency path exists.
+- Any emergency bypass must be recorded in court/evidence and must not silently mark release ready.
+
+## Emergency Owner Bypass
+
+Emergency bypass is allowed only as an owner-controlled event.
+
+Required evidence:
+
+- Reason for bypass.
+- Affected branch/PR/commit.
+- Commands or GitHub setting screenshots/readback.
+- Court note confirming why normal review could not be used.
+- Follow-up issue or report to restore normal governance.
+
+Bypass never equals release approval.
+
+## Evidence Commands
+
+Run before release or merge decisions:
+
+```powershell
+npm.cmd run github:audit
+gh api repos/trugurpala/pala-os-v6/branches/main --jq "{name,protected}"
+gh api repos/trugurpala/pala-os-v6/branches/main/protection --jq "{required_status_checks,required_pull_request_reviews,required_linear_history,allow_force_pushes,allow_deletions}"
+gh api repos/trugurpala/pala-os-v6/rulesets --jq ".[] | {name,target,enforcement,conditions,rules}"
+node src/cli.js court
+npm.cmd test
+```
+
+## Governance Lock
+
+Release, push, direct `main` write, branch-protection change, ruleset change, force-push, delete, deploy, and policy overwrite remain owner-controlled.
+
+Expected safe state until all evidence and owner approval exist:
+
+```text
+RELEASE_BLOCKED
+```
